And with me at the time I
was running this company

00:25:59.240 --> 00:26:02.590
with 170 people, with these
PeopleSoft consultants and all

00:26:02.590 --> 00:26:03.090
of that.

00:26:03.090 --> 00:26:05.630
And they said, don't even
know how you do that,

00:26:05.630 --> 00:26:06.690
because this is not you.

00:26:06.690 --> 00:26:08.960
So what they said
is with me, they

00:26:08.960 --> 00:26:12.250
said something that was
very core to my psyche

00:26:12.250 --> 00:26:17.830
is I like to play
games, but I like

00:26:17.830 --> 00:26:20.200
to play certain types of games.

00:26:20.200 --> 00:26:25.100
So I like to play games
where the outcome depends

00:26:25.100 --> 00:26:28.550
on my performance, it
doesn't depend on a team.

00:26:28.550 --> 00:26:33.909
So I wouldn't be a good guy
on a soccer team, for example.

00:26:33.909 --> 00:26:36.450
So they said that you like to
play games where the outcome is

00:26:36.450 --> 00:26:37.820
heavily dependent on you.

00:26:37.820 --> 00:26:42.730
And you like to play games
where you think with whatever

00:26:42.730 --> 00:26:46.250
you have to bring to
bear to that game,

00:26:46.250 --> 00:26:49.740
you have a likelihood
of winning.

00:26:49.740 --> 00:26:51.810
And when you pair
yourself, they said,

00:26:51.810 --> 00:26:55.310
with this game where
it seems to match up

00:26:55.310 --> 00:26:59.690
with the type of things you
like to do, then you'll kill it.

00:26:59.690 --> 00:27:07.310
So they said you need to focus
on driving that, feeding that.

00:27:07.310 --> 00:27:10.190
And this was just about two
or three months before Pabrai

00:27:10.190 --> 00:27:11.180
Funds was launched.

00:27:11.180 --> 00:27:13.060
And I had the idea for it.

00:27:13.060 --> 00:27:15.750
So I would explain to them what
I was trying to do about it.

00:27:15.750 --> 00:27:17.854
And they said, yes,
Pabrai Funds-- perfect.

00:27:17.854 --> 00:27:19.270
That's what you
should need to do.

00:27:19.270 --> 00:27:21.280
And they looked at
my other company,

00:27:21.280 --> 00:27:23.560
they said, as
quickly as possible,

00:27:23.560 --> 00:27:28.160
sell it, find the CEO,
whatever you can do, exit.

00:27:28.160 --> 00:27:28.870
And I did that.

00:27:31.630 --> 00:27:33.680
Like for example, I
love to play bridge.

00:27:33.680 --> 00:27:37.860
I spend five or six hours
a week playing bridge.

00:27:37.860 --> 00:27:38.950
And I look forward to it.

00:27:38.950 --> 00:27:42.980
Like Saturday and Sunday
I played about five hours

00:27:42.980 --> 00:27:43.490
of bridge.

00:27:43.490 --> 00:27:44.130
It was incredible.

00:27:44.130 --> 00:27:44.629
I loved it.

00:27:44.629 --> 00:27:49.762
Probably love it as much or
more than equity research.

00:27:49.762 --> 00:27:53.480
And you can see that.

00:27:53.480 --> 00:27:55.800
There's no reward
by playing bridge.

00:27:55.800 --> 00:27:58.100
But there is a reward
for me, because I only

00:27:58.100 --> 00:28:00.860
like to play duplicate bridge,
because in duplicate bridge

00:28:00.860 --> 00:28:02.140
we keep score.

00:28:02.140 --> 00:28:04.985
And if, for example, many of my
friends will say, hey, Mohnish,

00:28:04.985 --> 00:28:05.860
we're having a party.

00:28:05.860 --> 00:28:08.940
We're going to play
some social bridge.

00:28:08.940 --> 00:28:10.680
I have no interest
in social bridge.

00:28:10.680 --> 00:28:12.740
What's the point of
playing social bridge?

00:28:12.740 --> 00:28:14.510
There's no scorekeeping.

00:28:14.510 --> 00:28:18.040
And so scorekeeping just in
my psyche is very important.

00:28:18.040 --> 00:28:24.420
And so just I would say
that this whole area doesn't

00:28:24.420 --> 00:28:27.700
get covered in our
education system.

00:28:27.700 --> 00:28:32.990
I think universities ought
to pretty much give everyone

00:28:32.990 --> 00:28:34.100
their owner's manual.

00:28:34.100 --> 00:28:36.224
In fact, I think you should
get your owner's manual

00:28:36.224 --> 00:28:38.470
when you're 10 years old.

00:28:38.470 --> 00:28:45.040
And so to the extent that
individuals able to do that--

00:28:45.040 --> 00:28:47.460
and I think it's not very
